On International Women's Day, the President emphasizes the need for women and girls to have the same rights and freedoms as men. He acknowledges the contributions women make in various fields and highlights the importance of their involvement in the economy and politics. The President discusses the challenges faced by women globally, including child marriage and female genital mutilation, and emphasizes the importance of education in empowering girls. He mentions the Let Girls Learn initiative and announces the upcoming release of the U.S. Global Strategy to Empower Adolescent Girls. The President concludes by stating that investing in women and girls benefits the entire world and leads to a brighter, more peaceful, and prosperous future.